(Current Research in the Semantics/Pragmatics Interface 3),
Amsterdam/New York: Elsevier.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2002, &ldquo;Donkey Business&rdquo;,
<em>Linguistics and Philosophy</em>, 25(2): 129&ndash;156.
doi:10.1023/A:1014624331450</li>

<li>Geurts, Bart and Emar Maier, 2005, &ldquo;Quotation in
Context&rdquo;, <em>Hybrid Quotations</em> (<em>Belgian Journal of
Linguistics</em>, 17), Philippe de Brabaner (ed.), Amsterdam: John
Benjamins, 109&ndash;128. From a meeting in 2003.
doi:10.1075/bjl.17.07geu</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013, &ldquo;Layered Discourse
Representation Theory&rdquo;, in <em>Perspectives on Linguistic
Pragmatics</em> (Perspectives in Pragmatics, Philosophy &amp;
Psychology 2), Alessandro Capone, Franco Lo Piparo, and Marco
Carapezza (eds.), Cham/New York: Springer, 311&ndash;327.
doi:10.1007/978-3-319-01014-4_12</li>

<li>Groenendijk, Jeroen and Martin Stokhof, 1990, &ldquo;Dynamic
Montague Grammar&rdquo;, in <em>Papers from the Second Symposium on
Logic and Language</em>, L&aacute;szl&oacute; K&aacute;lm&aacute;n and
L&aacute;szl&oacute; P&oacute;los (eds.), Budapest: Akad&eacute;miai
Kiad&oacute;, 3&ndash;48.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1991, &ldquo;Dynamic Predicate
Logic&rdquo;, <em>Linguistics and Philosophy</em>, 14(1):
39&ndash;100. doi:10.1007/BF00628304</li>

<li>Heim, Irene R., 1982, <em>The Semantics of Definite and Indefinite
Noun Phrases</em>, PhD thesis, University of Massachusetts,
Amherst.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1990, &ldquo;E-Type Pronouns and Donkey
Anaphora&rdquo;, <em>Linguistics and Philosophy</em>, 13(2):
137&ndash;177. doi:10.1007/BF00630732</li>

<li>Hintikka, Jaakko, 1962, <em>Knowledge and Belief: An Introduction
to the Logic of the Two Notions</em> (Contemporary Philosophy),
Ithaca, NY: Cornell University Press.</li>

<li>Hobbs, Jerry R., 1979, &ldquo;Coherence and Coreference&rdquo;,
<em>Cognitive Science</em>, 3(1): 67&ndash;90.
doi:10.1207/s15516709cog0301_4</li>

<li>Hunter, Julie, 2013, &ldquo;Presuppositional Indexicals&rdquo;,
<em>Journal of Semantics</em>, 30(3): 381&ndash;421.
doi:10.1093/jos/ffs013</li>

<li>Janssen, Theo M.V., 1997, &ldquo;Compositionality&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#BM1997">van Benthem and ter Meulen 1997</a>:
 417&ndash;473 (ch. 7). doi:10.1016/B978-044481714-3/50011-4</li>

<li>Kamp, Hans, 1971, &ldquo;To the Memory of Arthur Prior Formal
Properties of &lsquo;Now&rsquo;&rdquo;, <em>Theoria</em>, 37(3):
227&ndash;273. doi:10.1111/j.1755-2567.1971.tb00071.x</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1981a, &ldquo;A Theory of Truth and
Semantic Representation&rdquo;, in <em>Formal Methods in the Study of
Language</em> (Mathematical Centre Tracts 135), Jeroen A. G.
Groenendijk, Theo M. V. Janssen, and Martin J. B. Stokhof (eds.),
Amsterdam: Mathematisch Centrum, 277&ndash;322.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1981b [2017], &ldquo;Ev&eacute;nements,
repr&eacute;sentations discursives et r&eacute;f&eacute;rence
temporelle&rdquo;, Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Nef (trans.),
<em>Langages</em>, 15(64): 39&ndash;64. The English original was
published in 2017 with additions from the French translation and
corrections as &ldquo;Events, Discourse Representations and Temporal
Reference&rdquo;, <em>Semantics and Pragmatics</em>, 10: article 2.
doi:10.3406/lgge.1981.1884 (French) doi:10.3765/sp.10.2 (English)</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1990, &ldquo;Prolegomena to a Structural
Account of Belief and Other Attitudes&rdquo;, in <em>Propositional
Attitudes: The Role of Content in Logic, Language, and Mind</em> (CSLI
Lecture Notes 20), C. Anthony Anderson and Joseph Owens (eds.),
Stanford, CA: CSLI Publications, 27&ndash;90.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1995, &ldquo;Discourse Representation
Theory&rdquo;, in <em>Handbook of Pragmatics. Manual</em> (Handbook of
Pragmatics 1), Jef Verschueren, Jan-Ola &Ouml;stman, and Jan Blommaert
(eds.), Amsterdam: J. Benjamins, 253&ndash;257.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2001a, &ldquo;The Importance of
Presupposition&rdquo;, in <em>Linguistic Form and Its Computation</em>
(Studies in Computational Linguistics), Christian Rohrer, Antje
Ro&szlig;deutscher, and Hans Kamp (eds.), Stanford, Calif: CSLI
Publications, 207&ndash;254.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2001b, &ldquo;Presupposition Computation
and Presupposition Justification: One Aspect of the Interpretation of
Multi-Sentence Discourse&rdquo;, in <em>Semantic and Pragmatic Issues
in Discourse and Dialogue: Experimenting with Current Dynamic
Theories</em> (Current Research in the Semantics/Pragmatics Interface
9), Myriam Bras and Laure Vieu (eds.), Amsterdam/New York: Elsevier,
57&ndash;84.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;Using Proper Names as
Intermediaries Between Labelled Entity Representations&rdquo;,
<em>Erkenntnis</em>, 80(S2): 263&ndash;312.
doi:10.1007/s10670-014-9701-2</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021, &ldquo;Sharing Real and Fictional
Reference&rdquo;, in <em>The Language of Fiction</em>, Emar Maier and
Andreas Stokke (eds.), Oxford: Oxford University Press, 37&ndash;87.
doi:10.1093/oso/9780198846376.003.0003</li>

<li>Kamp, Hans and Uwe Reyle, 1993, <em>From Discourse to Logic:
Introduction to Modeltheoretic Semantics of Natural Language, Formal
Logic and Discourse Representation Theory</em> (Studies in Linguistics
and Philosophy 42), Dordrecht/Boston: Kluwer Academic.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1996, &ldquo;A Calculus for First Order
Discourse Representation Structures&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Logic,
Language and Information</em>, 5(3&ndash;4): 297&ndash;348.
doi:10.1007/BF00159343</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;Discourse Representation
Theory&rdquo;, in <em>Semantics: An International Handbook of Natural
Language Meaning, Volume 1</em>, Claudia Maienborn, Klaus von
Heusinger, and Paul Portner (eds.), Berlin/Boston: De Gruyter Mouton,
872&ndash;923 (ch. 37).</li>

<li>Kamp, Hans and &Aacute;gnes Bende-Farkas, 2019, &ldquo;Epistemic
Specificity from a Communication-Theoretic Perspective&rdquo;,
<em>Journal of Semantics</em>, 36(1): 1&ndash;51.
doi:10.1093/jos/ffy005</li>

<li>Kamp, Hans and Antje Ro&szlig;deutscher, 1994,
&ldquo;DRS-Construction and Lexically Driven Inference&rdquo;,
<em>Theoretical Linguistics</em>, 20(2&ndash;3).
doi:10.1515/thli.1994.20.2-3.165</li>

<li>Kamp, Hans, Josef van Genabith, and Uwe Reyle, 2011,
&ldquo;Discourse Representation Theory&rdquo;, in <em>Handbook of
Philosophical Logic, Volume 15</em>, Dov M. Gabbay and Franz Guenthner
(eds.), Dordrecht: Springer Netherlands, 125&ndash;394.
doi:10.1007/978-94-007-0485-5_3</li>

<li>Kanazawa, Makoto, 1994, &ldquo;Weak vs. Strong Readings of Donkey
Sentences and Monotonicity Inference in a Dynamic Setting&rdquo;,
<em>Linguistics and Philosophy</em>, 17(2): 109&ndash;158.
doi:10.1007/BF00984775</li>

<li>Kaplan, David, 1989, &ldquo;Demonstratives&rdquo;, in <em>Themes
from Kaplan</em>, Joseph Almog, John Perry and Howard Wettstein (eds.),
New York: Oxford University Press, 481&ndash;563.</li>

<li>Karttunen, Lauri, 1973, &ldquo;Presuppositions of Compound
Sentences&rdquo;, <em>Linguistic Inquiry</em>, 4(2):
169&ndash;193.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1974, &ldquo;Presupposition and Linguistic
Context&rdquo;, <em>Theoretical Linguistics</em>, 1(1&ndash;3):
181&ndash;194. doi:10.1515/thli.1974.1.1-3.181</li>

<li>Krahmer, Emiel, 1998, <em>Presupposition and Anaphora</em> (CSLI
Lecture Notes 89), Stanford, CA: CSLI Publications.</li>

<li>Krifka, Manfred, 1996, &ldquo;Pragmatic strengthening in plural
predications and donkey sentences&rdquo;, in <em>Proceedings from
Semantics and Linguistic Theory (SALT 6)</em>, Teresa Galloway and
Justin Spence (eds.), pp. 136&ndash;153.
doi:10.3765/salt.v6i0.2769</li>

<li>Kripke, Saul A., 1979, &ldquo;A Puzzle about Belief&rdquo;, in
<em>Meaning and Use</em> (Synthese Language Library, 3), Avishai
Margalit (ed.), Dordrecht: Reidel, 239&ndash;283.
doi:10.1007/978-1-4020-4104-4_20</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1980, <em>Naming and Necessity</em>.
Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;Presupposition and Anaphora:
Remarks on the Formulation of the Projection Problem&rdquo;,
<em>Linguistic Inquiry</em>, 40(3): 367&ndash;386.
doi:10.1162/ling.2009.40.3.367</li>

<li>Lascarides, Alex and Matthew Stone, 2009, &ldquo;A Formal Semantic
Analysis of Gesture&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Semantics</em>, 26(4):
393&ndash;449. doi:10.1093/jos/ffp004</li>

<li>Maier, Emar, 2009a, &ldquo;Proper Names and Indexicals Trigger
Rigid Presuppositions&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Semantics</em>, 26(3):
253&ndash;315. doi:10.1093/jos/ffp006</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009b, &ldquo;Presupposing Acquaintance: A
Unified Semantics for <em>de dicto</em>, <em>de re</em> and <em>de
