32(5): 429&ndash;474. doi:10.1007/s10988-010-9065-2</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;Parasitic Attitudes&rdquo;,
<em>Linguistics and Philosophy</em>, 38(3): 205&ndash;236.
doi:10.1007/s10988-015-9174-z</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017, &ldquo;Fictional Names in
Psychologistic Semantics&rdquo;, <em>Theoretical Linguistics</em>,
43(1&ndash;2): 1&ndash;45. doi:10.1515/tl-2017-0001</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2023, &ldquo;Emojis as Pictures&rdquo;,
<em>Ergo an Open Access Journal of Philosophy</em>, 10: article 11.
doi:10.3998/ergo.4641</li>

<li>Montague, Richard, 1970, &ldquo;Universal Grammar&rdquo;,
<em>Theoria</em>, 36(3): 373&ndash;398.
doi:10.1111/j.1755-2567.1970.tb00434.x</li>

<li>Montague, Richard, 1974, <em>Formal Philosophy: Selected Papers of
Richard Montague</em>, Richard H. Thomason (ed.), New Haven, CT: Yale
